E. COLI EHEC - USA (33): (CALIFORNIA) MILITARY OUTBREAK, O157
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 2 Nov 2017
From: Anthony Hawksworth <anthony.w.hawksworth.ctr@mail.mil> [edited]


The serotype for the _E. coli_ outbreak is O157, with the production of Stx2 Shiga toxin. Twenty-one of 25 samples tested were positive.

As background, Naval Health Research Center (NHRC) San Diego conducts ongoing surveillance for respiratory and enteric illnesses at MCRD San Diego and other USA military basic training centers.

--
Communicated by:
Anthony Hawksworth
Surveillance Coordinator
Department of Operational Infectious Diseases
Naval Health Research Center
San Diego, CA
<anthony.w.hawksworth.ctr@mail.mil>

[ProMED thanks Anthony Hawksworth for the information regarding the isolate involved. It remains unclear why the case count appeared to drop by more than 100 in one day and whether the vehicle for transmission of the enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ is known or suspected. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5421203,204.]
